  "prompt": "How long can white wine last after it has been open?",
  "response": "The shelf life of opened white wine varies depending on several factors such as the type of wine, storage conditions, and the wine's exposure to air. On average, white wine can last between 3 to 5 days when stored in the refrigerator with a cork or wine stopper. However, it's important to note that the quality and taste may begin to degrade after the first day. Some higher-quality white wines, such as those with higher acidity or residual sugar, may last up to a week. To maximize its longevity, it's recommended to store the opened white wine upright in the fridge and limit the amount of air exposure.",
